## Team-Based Planning (Agent Teams)

For non-trivial features, spawn a planning Agent Team.

### Key rules
1. **Assign specific files** — each agent owns explicit file paths, no overlap
2. **Name recipients** — "Hey Backend Dev, see planning/scope.md"
3. **Max 3-5 members** — cost and coordination degrade beyond this
4. **Delegate mode** — lead coordinates only (Shift+Tab)
5. **Read-only until plan approved** — no code before PLAN.md sign-off

### When to use
- **Use teams**: Multi-file changes, new features, bug fixes requiring investigation, >2 concerns
- **Skip teams**: Single-file edits, typo fixes, config changes, simple renames
- **Use subagents instead**: tdd-runner, code-reviewer, deploy — sequential focused tasks

